# Extended-tier test suite — rare combinations, edge cases, regression bait.
# Each entry is a planned test file. Add the .sh, follow the smoke-tier
# pattern (source lib.sh; bootstrap; reset_state; aurox …; assert_*).
#
# The original backlog is fully landed/covered/retired as of 2026-07-16 —
# every note below records where each entry went. New planned tests go at
# the top of their section as `- name.sh (what it pins)` lines.
#
# PKGBUILD-driven cases:
#   (landed: 13_provides_virtual_resolves.sh — `-S myvirt` resolves through
#    by_provides to test-provides-virt, installed Explicit; the virtual is
#    satisfied with no literal myvirt package)
#   (landed: 14_install_hook_runs.sh — test-install-hook's post_install
#    scriptlet runs at the final pacman -U, proven by its marker file)
#   (graduated to smoke: epoch_dominates_version → smoke/40,
#    vcs_pkg_skipped_without_devel → smoke/41,
#    vcs_pkg_picked_up_with_devel → smoke/42)
#   (covered elsewhere: cycle_in_aur_deps_errors → smoke/22 (regular-depends
#    A↔B over test-cycle-a/b); split_pkg_with_intra_dep → smoke/06
#    (test-split-extras pulls its intra-split test-split-core);
#    split_pkg_partial_install → smoke/26 (one pkgname of a split installs
#    alone, siblings stay out))
#
# Resolver / planner:
#   (covered elsewhere: asdeps_overrides_direct → smoke/08 (`--asdeps` flips
#    the reason on a direct target); duplicate_targets_dedup → resolver unit
#    tests (BFS visited-dedup + the cross-bucket dedup pass))
#   (dropped: dep_constraint_versioned / dep_constraint_excluded /
#    target_with_version_constraint — aurox strips version constraints off
#    dep-specs and targets by design (lookup::strip_version_constraint,
#    unit-tested); there is no enforcement to exercise. Revisit if
#    constraints are ever honored.)
#
# State / idempotency:
#   (landed: 15_rebuild_after_artifact_deleted.sh — deleting the cached
#    .pkg.tar.zst flips smoke/43's artifact-derived check the other way:
#    the next -S reruns makepkg)
#   (landed: 16_declined_install_keeps_artifacts.sh — "n" at the elevation
#    gate keeps the built artifact; the retry hits "already built")
#   (landed: 17_sc_clears_worktrees.sh — -Sc forwards to pacman, empties
#    $STATE_DIR/pkgs, keeps installs; a later -S rebuilds cleanly)
#   (graduated to smoke: rebuild_cached_skips → smoke/43)
#
# Refresh:
#   (landed: 18_sy_incremental_fetch.sh — no-change -Sy says "no ref
#    updates"; after one branch bump the next -Sy fetches "1 ref(s)
#    updated" and search serves the new version. Found + fixed a fixture
#    bug: the mock AUR's bare-init HEAD dangled at refs/heads/master,
#    which breaks gix's update-refs pass on any update-carrying fetch —
#    setup-fixtures now points HEAD at the seed branch, matching GitHub's
#    always-resolvable default branch)
#   (landed: 19_syy_force_reclone.sh — the accepted branch: a canary file
#    in the mirror dir vanishes (wipe + re-clone) and the index rebuilds;
#    the declined branch is smoke/64)
#   (landed: 20_mirror_unreachable.sh — mirror moved away: -Sy fails
#    cleanly while -Ss serves the on-disk index and -S still builds from
#    the local clone; the dead-socket timeout half is extended/01)
#
# UX / flags:
#   (landed: 21_color_never_strips_ansi.sh — under script(1) PTYs:
#    Auto-on-TTY colors the aur prefix (control; needs TERM set), then
#    `color = "never"` emits zero escape bytes on the same TTY)
#   (landed: 24_help_for_unknown_op.sh — an op nobody owns fails loudly
#    with aurox's "unsupported aurox op" diagnostic, nonzero exit; known
#    pacman ops keep passing through)
#   (covered elsewhere: color_always_keeps_ansi → smoke/52 (`color =
#    "always"` forces ANSI onto a pipe); noconfirm_skips_prompts → the whole
#    suite runs TTY-less under --noconfirm — any prompt would hang a run —
#    and smoke/51 pins the confirm gating)
#
# Pacman pass-through:
#   (landed: 22_rns_removes_with_deps.sh — -Rns forwards elevated and takes
#    the orphaned dep with the target)
#   (landed: 23_u_install_local_file.sh — -U of a staged foreign artifact
#    forwards elevated and lands in the localdb)
#   (obsolete: syu_calls_pacman_first — `-Su`/`-Syu` are plain passthrough
#    now that the picker is gone; smoke/45 pins bare `aurox` → `-Syu`,
#    smoke/66 pins the `-Su` elevation)
#
# Concurrency:
#   (landed: 26_parallel_invocations_serialized.sh — two concurrent `-Sy`s
#    with the rootless repo sync on: the dbpath RefreshLock serializes the
#    critical section, no "unable to lock database" leaks, both exit 0,
#    and the raced mirror/index state stays servable)
#
# Failure modes:
#   (landed: 25_missing_dep_errors_with_hint.sh — a dep that resolves
#    nowhere (test-missing-dep) fails resolution naming the missing spec;
#    smoke/10 pins the unknown *target* flavor)
#   (covered elsewhere: makepkg_fails_stops_pipeline → superseded — failures
#    *isolate* rather than stop: smoke/28 (stratum sibling survives) +
#    smoke/29 (dependents skipped); corrupt_index_recoverable → load() maps
#    corrupt archive bytes to the same IndexIncompatible resync path that
#    smoke/49 (self-heal) + smoke/50 (--noresync) pin)
#
# Shell (REPL):
#   (landed: 07_shell_cart_apply.sh — add → gate → approve → apply, via the
#    shell_cart_e2e PTY driver)
#   (landed: 04_shell_upgrade_repo.sh — upgrade → preview+size-guard → apply, via
#    the shell_upgrade_e2e PTY driver; folds in the retired 05 size guard)
#   (landed: 08_shell_search_seed.sh — bare-term launch `aurox <term>` opens the
#    shell seeded with that search; add-by-number stages it, via the
#    shell_search_seed_e2e PTY driver)
#   (landed: 10_shell_info_repo.sh — `info` describes a sync-repo name from the
#    sync DBs (repo wins over a same-named AUR entry) and an AUR-only name from
#    the index, via the shell_info_e2e PTY driver)
#   (landed: 09_shell_undo.sh — number-follows-the-shown-list resolution,
#    `remove`'s refusal on a staged install, undo/redo, via the
#    shell_undo_e2e PTY driver)
#   (landed: 12_shell_first_launch.sh — the three-way first-launch AUR
#    question: Enter/Later persists nothing, `n` persists aur = false,
#    `refresh aur` bootstraps without a second question; via the
#    shell_bootstrap_{later,decline}_e2e drivers)
#   (landed: 27_shell_upgrade_aur_built_tag.sh — a pre-built new-version
#    artifact in the worktree flags the staged upgrade row `built`; ports the
#    retired 06_loop_built_tag, via the shell_built_tag_e2e PTY driver)
#   (landed: 28_shell_upgrade_provides_hint.sh — the dotnet shape: `upgrade`
#    seeds the outdated foreign virtual by its pkgname (the vercmp-newer one
#    stays out) and the review header carries `[provides <foreign>]`; found +
#    fixed the shell review dropping the hint (env::review_hint). Ports
#    retired smoke 33, via shell_provides_hint_e2e)
#   (landed: 29_shell_upgrade_split_sibling.sh — foreign split sibling:
#    `upgrade` + `apply` land only the picked sibling; ports retired smoke
#    44, via shell_split_sibling_e2e)
#   (landed: 30_shell_apply_failure_keeps_cart.sh — a failing build isolates:
#    the survivor installs, the fold keeps only the offender staged, `drop`
#    empties the cart at a live prompt; via shell_apply_failure_e2e)
#   (landed: 31_shell_ctrl_c_bails_to_prompt.sh — ^C down the PTY mid-build:
#    interrupted + cart kept + prompt resumes + clean quit, no orphaned build
#    child; via shell_ctrl_c_e2e. extended/02 pins the -S-path mechanics)
#   (landed: 32_shell_remove_stages_uninstall.sh — `remove` stages the
#    uninstall, show renders the "will remove" block, apply runs the
#    pacman -R lane; via shell_remove_e2e. 09_shell_undo pins the
#    refusal-on-staged-install half)
